      {
        "id": "6b2ef253615545f2b2885b43704e41e5",
        "analyst": "ACHOW",
        "analystUserId": "10023",
        "eventTypeCode": 1,
        "field": null,
        "fromValue": null,
        "toValue": null,
        "text": "2026-03-18 Good progress on modelling and few interim conclusions:\n1) Core earnings expansion is quite healthy if you strip out the one-offs in FY25, this in addition to layoffs should in theory control fixed cost vs a fast ramp in revenues \n2) Incremental profitability for business is healthy but there are a lot of misc costs that are a little hard to model, LEO ramp this year, how to think about AI revenue streams profitability for AWS, cost downs at retail \n3) Have not thought too hard about agentic AI impact on shopping which most see as negative but likely need to have a view on this - taking a step back also quite shocking that AMZN is able to grow GMV by like $60-70 bn a year in this environment, despite competition, and maybe worth also sanity checking this \n4) Need to think harder on discontinuous opportunities in AWS, at the current run-rate while growth is healthy, AMZN actually trades at a pretty reasonable multiple if you were to compare to CRWV / NBIS",
        "createBy": "10023",
        "updateBy": "10023",
        "createTime": "2026-03-18 14:52:17",
        "updateTime": "2026-03-18 14:52:17"
      },
